The paper focuses on developing a solution to make dynamic touchscreens accessible for blind people. This involves reverse engineering the underlying state diagrams of existing interfaces, generating conversational agents, and creating 3D-printed accessories. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Computer Vision (cs.CV) is also likely as the paper uses videos to reconstruct interfaces. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is relevant as the paper involves generating conversational agents. Robotics (cs.RO) is a possibility as the paper mentions 3D-printed accessories. Finally, Machine Learning (cs.LG) is a potential category as the paper may involve training models to recognize interface elements.
